Nekudot is written and maintained by:

  Barak Bloch <barak.bloch@gmail.com>

The core idea behind Nekudot — turning strokes into a web by connecting
nearby points — comes from Ricardo Cabello (mrdoob) and his Harmony sketch
tool (https://mrdoob.github.io/harmony/). Nekudot is an independent
reimplementation of that idea; credit for the original concept is his.

Copyright for the Nekudot source code is held by its contributors, listed
above. Authorship of individual changes is recorded in the git history.
See the README for license terms (GNU GPL v2).
